  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Assistance for the Fire Affected Rohingya Refugees</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A total of 11,000 households will be targeted in this response, consisting of an average 5 people per household (as per ISCG statistics). A total of 55,00 individuals will be reached through the project interventions with different support. Approximately 25,000 people will be directly covered through safe drinking water, sanitation and hygiene services and 2650 HHs will receive the NFI support. Protection component will target around 11,000  population and all beneficiaries will have an integrated support through increased health and hygiene awareness for COVID-19 crisis.</narrative>
  </description>
